FT  05 MAR 92 / Appointments: Non-executive directors
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
HILLSDOWN HOLDINGS continues to acknowledge the wishes of institutional
shareholders with the appointment of another outside director.
Sir Roy Griffiths, who retired as non-executive deputy chairman of J
Sainsbury last year, joins the Hillsdown board in a non-executive capacity.
Sir Roy became deputy chairman of Sainsburys in 1975 and was managing
director between 1979 and 1988.
The diversifed food group chaired by Sir Harry Salomon had not appointed any
outside directors until Sir John Nott was invited onto the board last
September. Tony Brice, formerly an executive director, is also a
non-executive director.
*****
Sir Leslie Porter at HELENE.
