<BYLINE>
   By VANESSA HOULDER, Property Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
British Aerospace and Asda, the supermarket group, have settled a dispute
about an option concerning the Burwood House Group, their property joint
venture.
The dispute flared after Arlington, BAe's property subsidiary, was forced to
pay the joint venture company Pounds 79m last month to fulfil an indemnity
agreement.
Asda argued that it had the right to exercise an option, that would force
BAe to buy it out, potentially for some Pounds 75m.
However, Arlington said the option was irrelevant, since it only applied in
the event of a default and was invalidated by the payment of Pounds 79m.
Asda said that the argument had been 'amicably settled.'
