In an interview in today's Glasgow Herald, the prime minister suggested that
the Budget could act as the springboard for recovery by boosting the
'confidence' factor in the economy.
He defended present levels of public borrowing as a 'cyclical' response to
the recession recalling that the Labour party had cut taxes in 1978 despite
a high borrowing requirement.
