<TEXT>
Burnfield lifted its profit by Pounds 550,000 in 1991, and following a big
reduction in exceptional costs, turned the previous pre-tax loss of Pounds
3.2m into a profit of Pounds 1.17m.
The company comprises two businesses: Isopad makes electric surface heating
systems, and Budenberg produces pressure gauges, calibration equipment and
thermometers.
Turnover was Pounds 20.6m, against Pounds 15.3m for the previous 11 months.
