<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAR 92 / The Lex Column: Alcatel/ITT
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Alcatel-Alsthom's purchase of ITT's minority stake in its telecoms
subsidiary is a logical conclusion to what was always couched as a
medium-term venture. On the face of it both parties benefit, ITT because it
is realising a Dollars 400m net profit, Alcatel because it can now
consolidate all the earnings of its most profitable division.
On closer inspection, though, Alcatel looks to have done the better of the
two. It is buying the stake at a multiple of around 12 times this year's
earnings. The generous structure of the cash payments should mean Alcatel
will avoid any dilution when it reports its 1991 results a month from now.
In addition, ITT's promise to hold its new shares for five years gives the
group a useful defensive edge. It is perhaps thus less surprising that
Alcatel's shares responded with a robust rise. In the race between Europe's
telecoms giants the gap between it and Siemens and the likes of Ericsson is
becoming ever wider.
